'''Pape Cherif Ndiaye''' (born 23 January 1996) is a Senegalese professional footballer who plays as a [[forward (association football)|forward]] for [[Süper Lig]] club [[Samsunspor]] and the [[Senegal national football team|Senegal national team]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.crvenazvezdafk.com/scc/vest/15354/serif-endiaje-novi-napadac-crvene-zvezde | title=Званична страница ФК Црвена звезда &#124; Најновије вести, утакмице и новости }}</ref>

==Club career==
Ndiaye joined Waasland-Beveren from the Senegalese club Grand Yoff FC.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rtbf.be/sport/football/belgique/jupilerproleague/detail_waasland-beveren-recrute-le-jeune-attaquant-cherif-ndiaye?id=9496147 |title=Waasland-Beveren recrute le jeune attaquant Cherif Ndiaye |website=Rtbf.be |date= 6 January 2017|accessdate=25 February 2017}}</ref> He made his debut for Waasland-Beveren in a 1–0 loss on 21 January 2017 to [[K.V. Oostende]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.maxifoot.fr/match/waasland-beveren-oostende-20170121.htm |title=BELGIQUE, Ligue Jupiler Waasland-Beveren-KV Oostende: 0 à 1 – Football – MAXIFOOT |website=Maxifoot.fr |date=20 August 1996 |accessdate=25 February 2017}}</ref>

===Turkey career===
Ndiaye played at [[Göztepe S.K.|Göztepe]] (2020–21, 2021–22 seasons) and [[Adana Demirspor]] (2022–23 half term, 2023) teams in Turkey. After going to China, SH Port, on 28 January 2023, Ndiaye returned to Turkey on loan to [[Adana Demirspor]] with an option to buy.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Adana Demirspor|url=https://www.facebook.com/AdsKulubu/posts/pfbid0ZfT5MktsLSthR76JdRhEujGLGRZE6qrstza5vni8RRgbsvN9xqLsvvemS6KJBDaFl|title=Takımımız, Çin Süper Lig ekiplerinden Shanghai Port takımının formasını giyen forvet oyuncusu Pape Cherif Ndiaye|date=28 January 2023|access-date=29 January 2023|language=tr}}</ref> He made a good performance by scoring 4 goals in 6 matches played by Adana Demirspor in the [[UEFA Europa Conference League]] qualifying round matches on 2023–24 season. The option to buy was exercised on 1 July 2023.

===Red Star Belgrade===
[[File:Cherif Ndiaye.jpg|left|thumb|Ndiaye lining up for [[Red Star Belgrade]] in 2024]]
After Adana Demirspor failed to qualify for the [[2023-24 UEFA Europa Conference League|UEFA Conference League]], Ndiaye's excellent start to the season did not go unnoticed. In the last minutes of 4 September, Ndiaye inks a three-year contract, with an option for another year, with the [[2023–24 UEFA Champions League|UEFA Champions League]] participant [[Red Star Belgrade]], in a transfer worth €4 million,<ref>{{cite news |title=Red Star Belgrade breaks transfer record with 4 million euro signing of Senegalese striker Cherif-Ndiaye |url=https://www.nogomania.com/article/Red-Star-Belgrade-breaks-transfer-record-with-4-million-euro-signing-of-Senegalese-striker-Cherif-Ndiaye |access-date=8 September 2023 |publisher=nogomania.com |date=4 September 2023}}</ref> along with Korean [[Hwang In-beom]]. In his new team, he made his [[2023–24 UEFA Champions League|UEFA Champions League]] debut against [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]] match.<ref>{{cite web |title=Man City:3-Crvena zvezda:1 |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/match/2039190--man-city-vs-crvena-zvezda/ |website=[[UEFA]] |access-date=20 September 2023}}</ref> His first score in that League is against [[BSC Young Boys|Young Boys]] on 4 October 2023.<ref>{{cite web |title=Crvena zvezda 2 - 2 Young Boys |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/match/2039112--crvena-zvezda-vs-young-boys/ |website=[[UEFA]] |access-date=5 October 2023}}</ref> 23 September 2024, he scored a [[hat-trick]] in the [[Eternal derby (Serbia)|Eternal derby]] against [[FK Partizan|Partizan Belgrade]] and becoming the first player to do so in 56 years since [[Stevan Ostojić]] on 17 November 1968.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.crvenazvezdafk.com/vesti/sherifov-het-trik-za-istoriju-vechitih-derbija|title=Шерифов хет-трик за историју вечитих дербија|website=FK Crvena zvezda|date=23 September 2024|accessdate=23 September 2024}}</ref>

==International career==
Ndiaye made his debut for the [[Senegal national football team|Senegal national team]] on 6 June 2024 in a [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification – CAF Group B|World Cup qualifier]] against [[DR Congo national football team|DR Congo]] at the [[Diamniadio Olympic Stadium]]. He substituted [[Nicolas Jackson]] in the 90th minute as the game ended in a 1–1 draw.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=ESPN|url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/match/_/gameId/687145/|title=Senegal v DR Congo game report|date=6 June 2024}}</ref>

